body.p: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON NORTHERN DIVISION
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION No. 5959 OF H. SAKAGUICHI ORDER WITHDRAWING FOR WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS EXHIBITS

It appearing to the Court that the above entitled cause has been concluded; and it further appearing, upon application of the United States Attorney, that the exhibits introduced by the Government as evidence herein have served their purpose; it is hereby
ORDERED that the exhibits, constituting the files and records of the Immigration Department, may be withdrawn from the custody of the Clerk of the Court for delivery to the United States Attorney.
DONE in open court this 1st day of April 1922
Received the above exhibits Apr 4 1922 THOS. P. REVELLE U.S. Attorney by C.L. Keen Clerk.
IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON Northern Division.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF H. SAKAGUICHI FOR WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS
FILED IN THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT Western District of Washington Northern Division APR 1 1922
F.M HARSHBERGER, Clerk By S.E. Leitch Deputy
